While it may require an extra set, the following is a lot more pythonic, and also finds the first missing positive in the same two passes that your code did (which is actually O(2n), and honestly made my eyes bleed trying to follow.)<p><pre><code>  def missPos(a):
      b={x for x in a}
      for x in range(1,len(b)+2):
          if not x in b:
              return x</code></pre>
